8. [decision] types/attestation.go TODO(#605) — rename As -> Attestation
   and AsCommand -> As. The core type has 110 importers; the most
   load-bearing noun in the codebase is not yet named. Settle or close.

15. [decision — later stage] Observe QNTX with its own primitives.
    Operational data currently lives in side tables outside the attestation
    model — storage_events (migration 010) and pulse_executions (migration
    007) have dedicated relational tables, queried by bespoke code and shown
    in bespoke panels. But QNTX exists to store time-stamped, attributed,
    provenanced claims — which is exactly what eviction events, job
    executions, and slow queries are. They could be attestations: queryable
    by ax, renderable by the existing glyph machinery, no bespoke tables or
    panels. The system would observe itself with its own primitives.
    Caveat: bounded-storage enforcement would evict observability data
    unless it is self-certified the way type attestations dodge enforcement
    (actor = own name) — so the side-table choice may be deliberate. A
    later-stage direction, noted here so it is not lost.

